#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:4
msgid "Availability"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:6
msgid ""
"The availability of super weapons can be restricted by other factors than"
" having a building providing the super weapon. The building almost "
"behaves as if it does not have this super weapon. For example, if a super"
" weapon is not accessible, EVA will not announce its detection once the "
"building is placed."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:11
msgid ""
"This does not affect the way :tag:`DisableableFromShell` works. Only the "
"super weapon set as :tag:`SuperWeapon` is checked for this tag, and the "
"building becomes unbuildable even if the super weapon is unavailable."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:15
msgid ""
"Even if all super weapons a building provides are disabled by whatever "
"restriction, it will still play the Super animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:24
msgid "Require a Country"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:26
msgid ""
"Access to super weapons can be restricted by the owning player's country."
" If the country is not one of the required houses or it is a forbidden "
"house, the super weapon will not become available and the cameo will "
"never appear."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:32
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.RequiredHouses=list of HouseTypes`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:31
msgid ""
"Specifies the houses that have access to this super weapon. All other "
"houses are forbidden from using it, and it will not become available for "
"them. Defaults to all houses."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:38
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.ForbiddenHouses=list of HouseTypes`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:35
msgid ""
"Specifies the houses that can never obtain this super weapon. All other "
"houses are not denied access to it, but they also have to satisfy the "
":tag:`SW.RequiredHouses` settings for it to become available. Defaults to"
" :value:`none`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:46
msgid "Auxiliary Buildings (:captiontag:`AuxBuilding`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:48
msgid ""
"The :tag:`AuxBuilding` feature was used in :game:`Tiberian Sun` to make "
"the Chemical Missile super weapon work. The Missile Silo provided both "
"the Multi Missile and the Chemical Missile, but the latter also required "
"the player to own a Tiberium Waste Facility to become available. "
":game:`Ares` expands this logic."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:53
msgid ""
"Multiple auxiliary building types are supported, and access to super "
"weapons can be removed again. This allows for two buildings to provide a "
"single super weapon and also to replace normal super weapons with "
"alternative versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:63
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.AuxBuildings=list of BuildingTypes`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:58
msgid ""
"Specifies the auxiliary buildings without which this super weapon cannot "
"become available. The player has to own at least one building of any of "
"these types to get access to this super weapon. Defaults to "
":value:`none`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:62
msgid ""
"Use this instead of the original :tag:`AuxBuilding` tag if you want to "
"have multiple auxiliary buildings."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:69
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.NegBuildings=list of BuildingTypes`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:66
msgid ""
"Specifies the negative auxiliary buildings whose presence will cause the "
"super weapon to become unavailable. This super weapon can become "
"available only if the player does not own any building of any of these "
"types. Defaults to :value:`none`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:71
msgid ""
"The original :tag:`AuxBuilding` tag now works well together with super "
"weapons provided by building upgrades. A super weapon on a building "
"upgrade will only become available if its :tag:`AuxBuilding` requirement "
"is satisfied."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:75
msgid ""
"Building upgrades do not constitute valid prerequisites for super weapons"
" and thus do not suffice :tag:`AuxBuilding`, :tag:`SW.AuxBuildings` or \\"
" :tag:`SW.NegBuildings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:79
msgid ""
"Super weapons using auxiliary building logics to restrict their "
"availability do not support building animations."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:88
msgid "Only for Human or AI Players"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:90
msgid ""
"Super weapons can be restricted to be used by houses controlled by human "
"or AI players only. This allows to hide special super weapons the AI "
"might use to gain an advantage from human players."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:96
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.AllowPlayer=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:95
msgid ""
"Whether this super weapon will be available to human players. Defaults to"
" :value:`yes`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:100
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.AllowAI=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:99
msgid ""
"Whether this super weapon will be available to AI players. Defaults to "
":value:`yes`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:108
msgid "Limited Number of Shots"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:110
msgid ""
"Super weapons can become unavailable after having been fired a certain "
"number of times. The super weapon cameo will disappear after the super "
"weapon became unavailable."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:117
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.Shots=integer`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:115
msgid ""
"How often this super weapon is allowed to fire before becoming "
"unavailable. Use :value:`-1` to allow unlimited firing. Is not supported "
"for Charge Drain super weapons. Defaults to :value:`-1`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:119
msgid ""
"Super weapons granted by crates or map actions will also count against "
"this limit. This might change in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:128
msgid "Always Granted Without Building"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:130
msgid ""
"With :game:`Ares` it is possible to use super weapons that are not tied "
"to a building that provides them. Instead, the always granted super "
"weapon will become immediately."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:134
msgid ""
"This setting still respects :tag:`AuxBuilding`, :tag:`SW.AuxBuidings`, "
":tag:`SW.NegBuildings`, :tag:`SW.ForbiddenHouses`, "
":tag:`SW.RequiredHouses`, :tag:`SW.AllowPlayer` and :tag:`SW.AllowAI`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:141
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.AlwaysGranted=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/availability.rst:139
msgid ""
"Whether this super weapon is not provided by any particular building but "
"is instead always available as long as the player has not been defeated. "
"Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

